          "html": "<div class=\"code-block\">MIDDLEWARE RateLimiter:\n    limits = {\n        \"/auth\":     {max: 5,  window: 60},\n        \"/balance\":  {max: 60, window: 60},\n        \"/transfer\": {max: 10, window: 60},\n        \"default\":   {max: 30, window: 60}\n    }\n    store = {}  // in-memory dictionary\n\n    FUNCTION handle(request):\n        key = request.user_id + \":\" + request.endpoint\n        limit = limits[request.endpoint] OR limits[\"default\"]\n\n        current = store.get(key, {count: 0, start: now()})\n        if now() - current.start &gt; limit.window:\n            current = {count: 0, start: now()}\n\n        current.count += 1\n        store[key] = current\n\n        if current.count &gt; limit.max:\n            return Response(429, {\"Retry-After\": ...})\n\n        return next(request)</div>\n<p class=\"text-sm\" style=\"margin-top:8px\"><strong>Algorithmusvergleich:</strong></p>\n<table class=\"comparison-table\"><thead><tr><th>Kriterium</th><th>Festes Fenster (gewählt)</th><th>Token Bucket</th></tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td>Genauigkeit</td><td>Kann 2&times; Limit an Grenzen erlauben</td><td>Glatt, keine Grenzprobleme</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Speicher</td><td>O(1) pro Schlüssel</td><td>O(1) pro Schlüssel</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Komplexität</td><td>Einfach</td><td>Mittel</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n",
